[maven] `Checkstyle` + Google Java Style = ❤ (#98)

* [maven] `Checkstyle` + Google Java Style = ❤

JMXFetch uses [Checkstyle](http://checkstyle.sourceforge.net/) with
[Google Java Style](http://google.github.io/styleguide/javaguide.html)
to enforce coding standards.

To perform a `Checkstyle` analysis and outputs violations, run:
```
mvn checkstyle::check
```

`Checkstyle` analysis is automatically executed prior to compiling the
code, testing.

More information: http://checkstyle.sourceforge.net/

[docs] Added info to README about how to test deployments

This was needed as the deployment local tests is not trivial to set up
without context. By having this here, we can ensure that it will be easy
to do again.

[build] Skip signing of artifacts for Travis/CircleCI builds

We don't need to sign the artifacts when doing testing so we added a
flag to activate a special profile if we are really releasing things.

[release] Preparing pom, README and CHANGELOG for 0.42.1

This release has no user-facing changes but it is required for us
to test end-to-end publishing to Sonatype.
